Qualifications:
1. Must be eligible to access the Laboratory in compliance with Section 3112 of the National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA). See Additional Information section below for details;
2. Recent Ph.D. in Machine Learning, Optimization, Computer Science, Mathematics or a related field;
3. Demonstrated ability and desire to obtain substantial domain knowledge in fields of application to enable effective communication with subject matter experts, and to identify novel, impactful applications of machine learning;
4. Experience developing, implementing and applying advanced statistical or machine learning models and algorithms using modern software libraries such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, or similar as evidence through medium to large scale deep learning models and experiments;
5. Demonstrated research productivity, as documented by publications, reports, presentations, and/or open-source software in relevant venues (NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, CVPR, AAAI, AISTATS, UAI, KDD, JMLR, Nature etc.);
